{
  "texts": [
    "Edge anomaly detection aims to identify edges in a dynamic graph that deviate from historical evolution patterns.",
    "Such irregularities may arise from connections that rogue users have introduced or manipulated maliciously.",
    "Conversely, node anomaly detection focuses on identifying nodes that distinctly differ from their peers or exhibit atypical behaviors.",
    "Anomaly detection has broad applications, particularly in fraud detection and ecommerce.",
    "For example, on e-commerce sites, users might manipulate the system by repeatedly clicking on specific products to increase their popularity artificially."
  ]
}